# 📌 Public IP vs Private IP

An **IP Address (Internet Protocol Address)** is a unique address assigned to every device connected to a network.

## 🌍 Public IP Address

A Public IP Address is assigned by an Internet Service Provider (ISP) and is accessible over the Internet.

### Features
- Globally unique
- Assigned by ISP
- Used for Internet communication
- Accessible from anywhere on the Internet
- Can be Static or Dynamic

### Examples
- 8.8.8.8
- 1.1.1.1
- 142.250.183.14

### Uses
- Hosting websites
- Email servers
- Cloud servers
- Remote access

---

## 🏠 Private IP Address

A Private IP Address is used only inside a Local Area Network (LAN). It cannot be accessed directly from the Internet.

### Private IP Ranges

| Class | IP Range |
|--------|--------------------------------|
| A | 10.0.0.0 – 10.255.255.255 |
| B | 172.16.0.0 – 172.31.255.255 |
| C | 192.168.0.0 – 192.168.255.255 |

### Examples
- 192.168.1.10
- 10.0.0.5
- 172.16.2.30

### Uses
- Home Wi-Fi
- Office Networks
- Internal communication

---

# 🔍 Public IP vs Private IP

| Feature | Public IP | Private IP |
|----------|-----------|------------|
| Scope | Internet | Local Network |
| Accessible from Internet | Yes | No |
| Assigned By | ISP | Router/DHCP |
| Unique | Globally Unique | Can Repeat |
| Security | Less Secure | More Secure |
| Cost | Provided by ISP | Free |

