# 🌐 OSI Model

The OSI (Open Systems Interconnection) Model is a conceptual networking model consisting of **7 layers**.

| Layer | Name | Function | Examples |
|--------|------|----------|----------|
| 7 | Application | User interaction | HTTP, HTTPS, FTP, SMTP, DNS |
| 6 | Presentation | Encryption & Compression | SSL/TLS, JPEG |
| 5 | Session | Session Management | NetBIOS, RPC |
| 4 | Transport | Reliable Data Transfer | TCP, UDP |
| 3 | Network | Routing | IP, ICMP |
| 2 | Data Link | MAC Addressing | Ethernet, ARP |
| 1 | Physical | Cables & Signals | Fiber, Wi-Fi, Copper |

---

## OSI Mnemonic

**All People Seem To Need Data Processing**

- Application
- Presentation
- Session
- Transport
- Network
- Data Link
- Physical

---

# 🌐 TCP/IP Model

The TCP/IP Model is the practical networking model used on the Internet.

| TCP/IP Layer | Corresponding OSI Layers | Protocols |
|---------------|--------------------------|-----------|
| Application | Application + Presentation + Session | HTTP, HTTPS, FTP, SMTP, DNS |
| Transport | Transport | TCP, UDP |
| Internet | Network | IP, ICMP |
| Network Access | Data Link + Physical | Ethernet, ARP, Wi-Fi |

---

# 📊 OSI vs TCP/IP

| OSI Model | TCP/IP Model |
|------------|--------------|
| 7 Layers | 4 Layers |
| Developed by ISO | Developed by DoD |
| Reference Model | Practical Model |
| Mainly for Learning | Used on the Internet |
| More Detailed | Simpler |

---

# 🔄 TCP vs UDP

| TCP | UDP |
|------|------|
| Connection-Oriented | Connectionless |
| Reliable | Faster |
| Ordered Delivery | Unordered Delivery |
| Error Checking | Minimal Error Checking |
| Slower | Faster |
| Used for HTTP, HTTPS, FTP | Used for DNS, Streaming, VoIP |

