# 🖥️ Useful Networking Commands

## Windows

```cmd
ipconfig
```

Displays IP configuration.

```cmd
ipconfig /all
```

Displays detailed network information.

```cmd
ping <IP>
```

Checks connectivity.

```cmd
tracert <IP>
```

Shows packet route.

```cmd
nslookup google.com
```

Looks up DNS records.

---

## Linux

```bash
ip addr
```

Shows network interfaces.

```bash
ifconfig
```

Displays interface information.

```bash
netstat -an
```

Shows active connections.

```bash
ss -tuln
```

Displays listening ports and services.

