# 📍 IP Logger

IP Logger is a tool that creates a tracking link. When someone opens the link, it records connection details.

### Information Collected
- Public IP Address
- Country
- City (Approximate)
- ISP
- Browser
- Operating System
- Device Type
- Date & Time
- Referrer (if available)

### Legitimate Uses
- Security Awareness
- Website Analytics
- Authorized Security Testing
- Digital Forensics

### Limitations
- Does NOT hack devices
- Does NOT reveal passwords
- Location is approximate, not exact

---

# 🐦 Canarytokens

Canarytokens are free security tokens that send an alert when someone accesses a protected or decoy resource.

### Types of Canarytokens
- URL Token
- PDF Token
- Microsoft Word Token
- DNS Token
- Email Token
- AWS Key Token
- QR Code Token
- Image/Web Bug Token

### Uses
- Detect unauthorized document access
- Monitor fake API keys
- Detect unauthorized file access
- Intrusion Detection
- Insider Threat Detection

### Advantages
- Free
- Easy to deploy
- Real-time alerts
- Helps detect attackers early

### Limitations
- Detects activity only after the token is triggered
- Does not prevent attacks
- Should be used with other security controls

---

# ⚖️ Ethical Use

Always use IP Logger, Canarytokens, and similar monitoring tools only:
- On systems you own.
- With explicit authorization.
- During approved security testing or training.
- In compliance with privacy laws and organizational policies.

